message: Scissors are your best friend for initial value generation! Always use scissors on individual soft ingredients (like paper, sponge, flower, mushroom, newspaper, ribbon, sunflower) first; this reliably turns them from 0 to 25. Once you have two 'cut' soft items, combine them. Aim to combine a 'natural, soft, cut' item with an 'artificial, soft, cut' item, as this combination has consistently yielded an 80-value item. Combining two 'artificial, soft, cut' items yielded 50. Do NOT use scissors on an already combined or high-value item, as this often leads to significant negative values. The 'frame' tool is very risky; it can sometimes increase value from 50 to 70 if used once, but repeated framing often leads to losses or zero value, even at high scores. Once you achieve an 80-value item, it's generally safest to submit immediately to secure the high score.

message: Hello future player! Here are some key learnings: Scissors are great for 'soft' items (both natural and artificial), always turning their value from 0 to 25. Avoid using scissors on 'hard' items, as it seems to result in negatives. The most effective combination is 'natural, soft, cut' + 'artificial, soft, cut', which yields an item with 80 value. Once you have an item valued at 80 or higher, use the 'frame' tool on it to reach 100. Framing on lower values is very risky and often results in huge losses. message: Always use scissors on soft ingredients first; they consistently give 25 value. The best combination for high value (80) is a 'cut natural, soft' item with a 'cut artificial, soft' item. Once you have an item worth 80, use the 'frame' tool on it to achieve 100. Avoid combining more than two items, as 'overcomplicated' items often result in negative or very low values. Scissors on hard items resulted in negatives. Framing is extremely risky at low scores but can be a last resort if your score is 0 to get a small positive value, as it cannot drop below 0.

message: Scissors are excellent for soft items, providing +25 value whether natural or artificial. The most reliable high-value combination is a 'cut natural soft' item with an 'artificial soft' item (e.g., cut flower + ribbon) for +55. If you have an item around 55 value, using the frame tool on it can boost it to 75. Avoid combining more than two items or introducing 'hard' features, as this often leads to 'overcomplicated' items with significant negative values. Use the frame sparingly on low-value items; it's safest for higher-value soft combinations.
